<DOC><DOCNO> AP890122-0067 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-01-22-89 1904EST</FILEID><FIRST>r i AM-Iran-Smoking     01-22 0094</FIRST><SECOND>AM-Iran-Smoking,0096</SECOND><HEAD>Kurdistan Province Gives Up Smoking For A Day</HEAD><DATELINE>NICOSIA, Cyprus (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   Iran's Kurdistan province held a``no-smoking'' day on to encourage tobacco addicts to give up thehabit, the Islamic Republic News Agency reported Sunday.   The agency, monitored in Nicosia, said smoking was banned ingovernment offices and public places on Saturday under an agreementbetween a local tobacco company and the Physical TrainingOrganization.   It said stores stopped selling tobacco products.   Kurdistan was the third province in the past three months toorganize a ``no-smoking'' day, the agency said.</TEXT></DOC>